headline: SWK Q4 Deep Dive: Margin Expansion and Tariff Mitigation Amid Revenue Pressures
summary: Manufacturing company Stanley Black & Decker (NYSE:SWK) missed Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q4 CY2025, with sales flat year on year at $3.68 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.41 per share was 9.9% above analysts’ consensus estimates.
